==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squeaker
<hw>Squeak"er</hw> <pr>(-⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who, or that which, squeaks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The Australian gray crow shrike
(<spn>Strepera anaphonesis</spn>); -- so called from its note.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A contest won by a small margin.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A narrow escape from harm.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squeakingly</ent>⟦br⟧
